<section class="about-section">
  <div class="about-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="about-label">About the Portal</div>
      <h2>Unlocking the genetic heritage of Philippine rice</h2>
      <div class="about-accent"></div>
      <p>
        The 1001 Philippine Rice Genome Portal is a Tripal-powered bioinformatics
        platform developed to catalogue, manage, and share whole-genome sequencing
        data of rice varieties collected across the Philippine archipelago.
      </p>
      <p>
        Built in collaboration with IRRI, DA-PhilRice, UPLB, and partner agencies,
        this resource supports research in varietal improvement, disease resistance,
        climate adaptation, and conservation of indigenous rice germplasm.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-visual">
      <div class="genome-grid" id="genome-grid"></div>
      <div class="about-visual-label">Genome variant density visualisation</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

